Super Eagles and CD Leganes defender, Kenneth Omeruo has continued to make waves on headlines over wonderful performances in his in Spanish club side,recently  he welcomes his first child with his wife, Chioma.
National Daily learnt that the couple, who got married in 2017 before completing the wedding rites earlier this year in Turkey, join the ever-growing list of current Eagles players who have added more caps off the field with the likes of Troost-Ekong, Moses Simon and Ogenyi Onazi giving birth this year.
The on-loan Chelsea defender and his wife confirmed that  “It’s a girl.
He went on to say, I’m grateful for this wonderful blessing upon my family and I want to thank God Almighty for making me witness such a great day”.
